column1: #Text=She 's too skinny and the crying gets annoying !
#Text=" Was hiding your anorexia the reason why you were as emotional as you were ?
#Text=AM :
#Text=The bonding was completely TV material and not really there .
#Text=MH :
#Text=Which judge do you feel was perhaps the most genuine in terms of behavior on-screen and off ?
#Text=AM :
#Text=Tricia Helfer and Ron ( one of the producers ) .
#Text=MH :
#Text=There 's been criticism on America 's Next Top Model that Tyra Banks and the care that she shows to her models is an act for TV .
#Text=Do you think Tricia Helfer is the opposite ?
#Text=AM :
#Text=Absolutely , and do n't you think it is weird that she no longer hosts CNTM ?
#Text=MH :
#Text=Jay Manuel now hosts , and it 's weird to see because he 's in a different mode than he is on America 's Next Top Model , where he 's often very blunt and sarcastic . [ ... ]
#Text=Toward the end , there was a lot of rather cruel teasing towards you coming from Alanna and Brandi .
#Text=As you may remember , it culminated in the night they went through your belongings and then tampered with a " treat " they prepared for you and Sisi .
#Text=It was n't a complete 180 in behavior , per se , but it did get very nasty very quickly .
#Text=Why do you think they acted the way they did ?
#Text=Also , you were never shown confronting them for what they did .
#Text=Did you end up doing so ?
#Text=Finally , did you know the extent of all they had done right away , or did you not find out until you actually saw the episode on television ?
